text: Willowbrook is a city in Reno County, Kansas, United States, and a suburb of Hutchinson. As of the 2020 census, 71 people lived there. == Geography == Willowbrook is at (38.101109, -97.991984). According to the United States Census Bureau says that the city has a total area of . All of it is land. == Demographics == === 2020 census === As of the 2020 census, there were 71 people, 28 households, and 21 families living in Willowbrook. All of the households owned their home. The median age was 63.8 years. Of the people, 98.6% were White and 1.4% were Pacific Islanders. None were Hispanic or Latino. === 2010 census === As of the 2010 census, there were 87 people, 35 households, and 33 families living in the city. == References == == Other websites == ;City * Willowbrook - Directory of Public Officials ;Schools * USD 308, local school district ;Maps * Willowbrook City Map , KDOT Category:Cities in Reno County, Kansas
